<div id="review_8326072" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/8326072" />
    <a title="Anne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/546484-anne"><img alt="Anne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1500388520p2/546484.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/8326072?book_show_action=true">Oct 27, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anne" href="/user/show/546484-anne">Anne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780552772501" href="/book/show/870989.Q_A">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer8326072" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9522948008391827499">I finished reading Q&amp;A this morning, a thoroughly enjoyable read and a real page-turner. If the film, Slumdog Millionaire, based on this novel is anywhere near as good, then it will be one to watch.<br/><br/> Q&amp;A begins with Ram as the winner of the largest prize in a TV quiz show, he is arrested on the grounds of cheating as nobody believes that a waiter in a restaurant in Mumbai could possibly answer all twelve questions correctly.<br/><br/>The following twelve chapters are based on incidents that have happened i</span>
  <span id="freeText9522948008391827499" style="display:none">I finished reading Q&amp;A this morning, a thoroughly enjoyable read and a real page-turner. If the film, Slumdog Millionaire, based on this novel is anywhere near as good, then it will be one to watch.<br /><br /> Q&amp;A begins with Ram as the winner of the largest prize in a TV quiz show, he is arrested on the grounds of cheating as nobody believes that a waiter in a restaurant in Mumbai could possibly answer all twelve questions correctly.<br /><br />The following twelve chapters are based on incidents that have happened in Ram's short, but very full life. Each incident relates to a question in the quiz. This is a really unique way of writing a novel, but it really works. The events are not in chronological order but each chapter is a suspenseful story of it's own.<br /><br />This is a beguiling blend of high comedy, drama, and romance that reveals how we know what we know — not just about trivia, but about life itself. Looking at humanity in all its squalor and glory, Vikas Swarup presents a vision of the struggle between good and evil — and what happens when one boy has no other choice in life but to survive.<br /><br />An excellent read. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9522948008391827499" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


